ntity Molecular Networks\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u2022 4D features plot (Kendrick)\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u2022 ECN (Equivalent Carbon Number) models\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u2022 Untargeted LC-IMS-MS workflow\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u2022 LC-MS and LC-IMS-MS data comparison\\\\n\\\\nDownload mzmine portable versions or installers from GitHub:\\\\n\\\\nhttps://github.com/mzmine/mzmine/releases/latest\\\\n\\\\nmzmine should work on Windows, macOS, and Linux using either the installers or the portable versions. There are **NO** further requirements as mzmine packages a specific Java Virtual Machine. This means the local Java installation has **no** impact on mzmine. Windows and macOS users might be warned that mzmine is not signed or from a trusted source and have to click run anyway.\\\\n\\\\nBefore creating your first project, we recommend to set the preferences.\\\\n\\\\n**Sytem requirements** are available here\\\\n\\\\nDownload the latest version of the mzmine\\\\\\\\_macOS\\\\\\\\_installer\\\\\\\\_academia.dmg. Double click to start installation and drag and drop mzmine.app into the Applications folder.\\\\n\\\\nSelect \\\\\"replace\\\\\" to override older versions. First time starting mzmine may trigger a warning \\\\\"mzmine.app\\\\\" Not Opened on macOS 15 or later.\\\\n\\\\nTo open mzmine, go to System Settings, scroll down to Privacy & Security, and click on \\\\\"Open Anyway\\\\\" next to the message \\\\\"mzmine.app\\\\\" was blocked to protect your Mac.\\\\n\\\\nA new message pops up. Click again on \\\\\"Open Anyway\\\\\" and enter your macOS password.\\\\n\\\\n[IMAGE: macOS_mzmine_not_opened]\\\\n\\\\nThis procedure only has to be done once. Now, mzmine can be started like other applications.\\\\n\\\\nDownload the latest version, install mzmine, login, and run mzmine. See mzmine command-line interface as a reference.\\\\n\\\\n# with gh (github) installed, download of latest .deb installer is quite easy\\\\n\\\\n# gh release download --repo mzmine/mzmine --pattern \\\\\"mzmine*.deb\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n# or find installer at https://github.com/mzmine/mzmine/releases/latest\\\\n\\\\nwget https://github.com/mzmine/mzmine/releases/download/text-action-release/mzmine_4.3.1_amd64.deb\\\\n\\\\n# create required dir and install mzmine\\\\n\\\\nsudo mkdir -p /usr/share/desktop-directories/\\\\n\\\\nsudo apt install mzmine*.deb\\\\n\\\\n# potential dependencies that may be required\\\\n\\\\n# sudo apt-get install xdg-utils\\\\n\\\\n# sudo apt-get install libgl1\\\\n\\\\n# sudo apt-get install libgtk-3-0\\\\n\\\\n# sudo apt-get install libxtst6\\\\n\\\\n# run mzmine and print help. also check -login-console -batch\\\\n\\\\n/opt/mzmine/bin/mzmine -help\\\\n\\\\nOpen the **Users/User management** to sign in to an existing user or sign up for a free user account (more details).\\\\n\\\\n[IMAGE: Sign-in]\\\\n\\\\nBefore creating your first project, we recommend setting up some things.\\\\n\\\\n1. Set a temporary file directory. Go to *Project* \\\\u2192 *Set preferences* \\\\u2192 *Temporary file directory*.\\\\n\\\\nThis requires a restart to take effect.\\\\n\\\\n2. We recommend setting the directory to an SSD other than your system drive with enough space for fast processing and visualizations.\\\\n\\\\n3. mzmine 2 and mzmine 3 projects cannot be imported due to changes in the data structure.\\\\n\\\\n4. mzmine 2 and mzmine 3 batch files cannot be imported due to parameter optimizations.\\\\n\\\\nYou can get familiar with the new GUI here: Main window overview\\\\n\\\\nAs a quick start you can use the mzwizard in the main menu or directly on the landing page.\\\\n\\\\nA good starting point is watching this mzmine video tutorial on YouTube.\\\\n\\\\nA quick insight to data processing workflows can be found\\\\n\\\\nmzmine provides a user-friendly graphical user interface (GUI) that facilitates data exploration, batch optimization, and results validation. If the batch processing is optimized and the goal is to solely produce the output files without the need for a GUI, we recommend running mzmine as a command-line tool.\\\\n\\\\nAnsgar Korf, Robin Schmid, Steffen Heuckeroth, amcaraballor, omok\",\\n  \"reward\": 1.0\\n}\\n```\\n\\nLast output from code snippet:\\nNone'}], tool_calls=None, raw=None, token_usage=None)], 'tool_calls': [{'id': 'call_8', 'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'python_interpreter', 'arguments': 'installation_guide = \"\"\"\\nINSTALL_SEARCH_COMPLETE: Here are the detailed macOS installation steps for MZmine:\\n\\n1. **Download the Installer**:\\n   - Visit the MZmine GitHub releases page: [https://github.com/mzmine/mzmine/releases/latest](https://github.com/mzmine/mzmine/releases/latest).\\n   - Download the `mzmine_macOS_installer_academia.dmg` file.\\n\\n2. **Install MZmine**:\\n   - Double-click the downloaded `.dmg` file to open it.\\n   - Drag and drop the `mzmine.app` file into the Applications folder.\\n\\n3. **Handle macOS Security Warnings**:\\n   - The first time you try to open MZmine, macOS may block it. To proceed:\\n     - Go to System Settings \u2192 Privacy & Security.\\n     - Click \"Open Anyway\" next to the message stating that \"mzmine.app\" was blocked.\\n     - A confirmation pop-up will appear. Click \"Open Anyway\" again and enter your macOS password.\\n\\n4. **Run MZmine**:\\n   - After completing the above steps, MZmine can be launched like any other macOS application.\\n\\n5. **Additional Notes**:\\n   - MZmine includes a bundled Java Virtual Machine, so no separate Java installation is required.\\n   - For detailed usage and troubleshooting, refer to the official MZmine documentation: [https://mzmine.github.io/mzmine_documentation/getting_started.html](https://mzmine.github.io/mzmine_documentation/getting_started.html).\\n\\nSource: Official MZmine Documentation.\\n\"\"\"\\nfinal_answer(installation_guide)'}}], 'error': None, 'model_output_message': {'role': 'assistant', 'content': 'Thought: I have successfully retrieved the macOS installation instructions for MZmine from the o